                            <comment id="14104132" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 20 Aug 2014 17:03:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mshuler&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mshuler&quot;&gt;mshuler&lt;/a&gt; to review&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14109969" author="mshuler" created="Mon, 25 Aug 2014 23:22:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This looks fine to me - it appears that this was not added after jsvc was removed, so it seems a fine idea to add for picking up extra options from /etc/cassandra/default when a user doesn&apos;t wish to modify cassandra-env.sh&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14110852" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 26 Aug 2014 15:46:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14339364" author="mshuler" created="Thu, 26 Feb 2015 23:00:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mattrobenolt&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mattrobenolt&quot;&gt;mattrobenolt&lt;/a&gt; just an FYI that this export of the JVM_OPTS is going to be removed from the init script and /etc/default/cassandra is going to get some additional comments that conf/cassandra-env.sh is really the correct place to add/modify your JVM options.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
